tegory:20th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English writers]]\n[[Category:American magazine editors]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:People who lost United States citizenship]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Oxford Union]]\n[[Category:People educated at Ashdown House]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:English Anglicans]]\n[[Category:American Anglicans]]\n[[Category:20th-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:Converts to Anglicanism from Roman Catholicism]]\n[[Category:Christians from Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Christians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:English people of American descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:People from Crouch End]]\n[[Category:People from Maida Vale]]\n[[Category:People from Uccle]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Writers from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Politicians from New York City]]\n[[Category:Writers from New York City]]\n[[Category:People from the Upper East Side]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2019\u2013]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the European Schools]]\n", "name_user": "Joseph2302", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Johnson"}
{"title_page": "Steneosaurus", "text_new": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = [[Middle Jurassic|Middle]] or [[Late Jurassic]]<br />~{{Fossil range|Callovian|Oxfordian|[[Callovian]] or Lower [[Oxfordian (stage)|Oxfordian]]}}\n| image = Steneosaurus Holzmaden.jpg\n| image_caption = '''Steneosaurus' bollensis'', Holzmaden Germany\n| taxon = Steneosaurus\n| authority = [[\u00c9tienne Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire|Geoffroy]], 1825\n| type_species = {{extinct}} '''''Steneosaurus rostromajor'''''\n| type_species_authority = Geoffroy, 1825\n| subdivision_ranks = Assigned species\n| subdivision =\n* '''S.' baroni'' {{small|Newton 1893}}\n* '''S.' bollensis'' {{small|(Jaeger 1828)}}\n* '''S.' edwardsi'' {{small|(Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868)}}\n* '''S.' gracilirostris'' {{small|Westphal 1961}}\n* '''S.' heberti'' {{small|Morel de Glasville 1876}}\n* '''S.' leedsi'' {{small|Andrews 1909}}\n* '''S.' megistorhynchus'' {{small|(Geoffrey Saint-Hilaire in Eudes-Deslongchamps 1869)}}\n* '''S.' pictaviensis'' {{small|Vignaud 1998}}\n| synonyms =\n{{collapsible list|bullets = true\n |title=<small>'''Synonyms of ''Steneosaurus'''''</small>\n| ?''[[Macrospondylus]]'' {{small|[[Christian Erich Hermann von Meyer|Von Meyer]] 1830}}\n| ''Leptocranius'' {{small|Bronn 1837}} }}\n{{collapsible list|bullets = true\n |title=<small>'''Synonyms of ''S. rostromajor''''':</small>\n| ''Gavialis bacheleti''\n| ''Steneosaurus longirostris'' }}\n}}\n\n'''''Steneosaurus''''' is a [[Nomen dubium|dubious]] [[genus]] of [[Teleosauridae|teleosaurid]] [[crocodyliform]] from the [[Middle Jurassic|Middle]] or [[Late Jurassic]] ([[Callovian]] or early [[Oxfordian (stage)|Oxfordian]]) of [[France]]. The genus has been used as a [[wastebasket taxon]] for thalattosuchian fossils for over two centuries, and almost all known historical species of teleosauroid have been included within it at one point. The genus has remained a wastebasket, with numerous species still included under the label ''\u2018Steneosaurus\u2019'', many of which are unrelated to each other (either [[paraphyletic]] or [[polyphyletic]] with respect to each other and other genera of teleosauroids).\n\nThe [[type species]], '''''S. rostromajor''''', was only formally recognised as such in 2020, and this revision determined the [[type specimen]] of ''Steneosaurus'' was undiagnostic, and so declared the genus ''Steneosaurus'' a ''nomen dubium''. The remaining species referred to ''Steneosaurus'' thus require new generic names, and some species have already been assigned to new genera prior to ''Steneosaurus'' being declared a ''nomen dubium''.<ref name=\"revised\">{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=M. M. |last2=Young |first2=M. R. |last3=Brusatte |first3=S. L. |year=2020 |title=Emptying the wastebasket: a historical and taxonomic revision of the Jurassic crocodylomorph ''Steneosaurus'' |journal=Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society |issue=zlaa027 |doi=10.1093/zoolinnean/zlaa027}}</ref>\n== Species ==\n[[File:Steneosaurus durobrivensis 45.jpg|thumb|right|250px|'''S.' edwardsi'' skull]]\nSpecies in this genus are traditionally classed into two skull groups: longirostrine (long, narrow jaws) and mesorostrine (slightly shorter jaws).\n\n;Longirostrine\n* '''S.' atelestatus'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381015 ''Steneosaurus atelestatus''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Oxfordian [[Marnes de Villers Formation]] of France\n* '''S.' baroni'' - [[Bathonian]] [[Oolite Formation|Oolite]] and [[Kandreho Formation]]s of [[Madagascar]]\n* '''S.' blumembachi'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381016 ''Steneosaurus blumembachi''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Oxfordian Marnes de Villers Formation of France\n* '''S.' bollensis'' - Toarcian [[Alum Shale Formation|Alum Shale]] and [[Jet Rock Formation]]s of England and [[Posidonia Shale]] of Germany\n* '''S.' gracilirostris'' - Toarcian Alum Shale of England\n* '''S.' heberti'' - Callovian Etrochey vertebrate layer (C\u00f4te-d'Or) of France\n* '''S.' leedsi'' - Callovian Oxford Clay of England\n* '''S.' megistorhynchus'' ([[type species|type]]) - Bathonian [[Forest Marble Formation]] of England and Great Oolite Formation of France\n* '''S.' oplites'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1863<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381014 ''Steneosaurus oplites''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Toarcian La Caine-Curcy of France\n* '''S.' pictaviensis'' - Callovian Les Lourdines in France\n* '''S.' rudis'' {{small|Sauvage 1874<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=89217 ''Steneosaurus rudis''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - France\n\n;Mesorostrine\n* '''S.' bouchardi'' - {{small|Sauvage 1872}}, Kimmeridgian\u2013Tithonian of France\n* '''S.' edwardsi'' - Callovian [[Marnes de Dives]] Formation, Le Wast and Les Lourdines in France and [[Oxford Clay]] of England\n\nAdditional ''Steneosaurus'' fossils not attributed to a specific genus have been found in:\n* Bathonian [[El Mers Formation]], Morocco\n* Bathonian [[Techout Formation]], Tunisia\n* Jurassic Czarnoglowy, Poland\n\n=== Reassigned species ===\n* '''Steneosaurus' boutilieri'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1869}} = ''[[Yvridiosuchus]]''<ref name=Johnson19>{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=Michela M. |last2=Young |first2=Mark T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=Stephen L. |year=2019 |title=Re-description of two contemporaneous mesorostrine teleosauroids (Crocodylomorpha: Thalattosuchia) from the Bathonian of England and insights into the early evolution of Machimosaurini |journal=[[Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society]] |volume=in press |issue= |pages= |doi=10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz037 }}</ref>\n* '''Steneosaurus' brevior'' {{small|Blake, 1876}} = ''[[Mystriosaurus]]''\n* '''Steneosaurus' deslongchampsianus'' {{small|(Lennier 1887)<ref name=Foffa2018>{{cite journal |last=Foffa |first=Davide |last2=Young |first2=Mark T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=Stephen L. |year=2018 |title=Filling the Corallian gap: New information on Late Jurassic marine reptile faunas from England |url=http://www.app.pan.pl/archive/published/app63/app004552018.pdf |journal=[[Acta Palaeontologica Polonica]] |volume=63 |pages=287\u2013313 |accessdate=2019-03-07 |doi=10.4202/app.00455.2018}}</ref>}}\n* '''Steneosaurus' larteti'' {{small|(Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868)}} = ''[[Deslongchampsina]]''<ref name=Johnson19/>\n* '''Steneosaurus' megarhinus'' {{small|(Hulke 1871)}} = ''[[Bathysuchus]]''<ref>{{cite journal |last=Foffa |first=D. |last2=Young |first2=M.T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=S.L. |last4=Steel |first4=L. |year=2015 |title=New specimen and revision of the late Jurassic teleosaurid 'Steneosaurus' megarhinus |url=https://peerj.com/preprints/1351/ |journal=[[PeerJ Preprints]] |volume=3 |pages=e1351v1 |accessdate=2019-03-07}}</ref><ref name=Foffa19>{{cite journal |last1=Foffa |first1=D. |last2=Johnson |first2=M.M. |last3=Young|first3=M.T. |last4=Steel |first4=L. |last5=Brusatte |first5=S.L. |date=2019 |title=Revision of the Late Jurassic deep-water teleosauroid crocodylomorph ''Teleosaurus megarhinus'' Hulke, 1871 and evidence of pelagic adaptations in Teleosauroidea. |journal=[[PeerJ]] |volume=7 |pages=e6646 |doi=10.7717/peerj.6646 |pmid=30972249 |pmc=6450380}}</ref>\n* '''Steneosaurus' obtusidens'' {{small|Andrews 1909}} = ''[[Lemmysuchus]]''\n\n== Evolutionary relationships ==\nA 2005 [[phylogenetic]] analysis into the evolutionary relationships of [[Thalattosuchia]] did not support the [[monophyly]] of ''Steneosaurus'', as the genera ''[[Machimosaurus]]'' and ''[[Teleosaurus]]'' both fell within ''Steneosaurus''.<ref name=\"Mueller-T\u00f6we, 2005\">{{cite journal |last=Mueller-T\u00f6we |first=I. J. |year=2005 |title=Phylogenetic relationships of the Thalattosuchia |journal=Zitteliana |volume=A45 |issue= |pages=211\u2013213 |url=http://epub.ub.uni-muenchen.de/11958/1/zitteliana_2005_45_09.pdf }}</ref> Reinforcing the paraphyly of ''Steneosaurus'', the Callovian species ''\"Steneosaurus\" obtusidens'' has been recovered as the sister species of ''Machimosaurus'' in recent cladistic analyses of Thalattosuchia and renamed ''[[Lemmysuchus]]'', while '''Steneosaurus' bollensis'' was recovered in a basal position to other members of ''Steneosaurus sensu lato''.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = M. T. | last2 = Brusatte | first2 = S. L. | last3 = De Andrade | first3 = M. B. | last4 = Desojo | first4 = J. B. | last5 = Beatty | first5 = B. L. | last6 = Steel | first6 = L. | last7 = Fern\u00e1ndez | first7 = M. S. | last8 = Sakamoto | first8 = M. | last9 = Ruiz-Ome\u00f1aca | first9 = J. I. | last10 = Schoch | first10 = R. R. | year = 2012 | title = \"Butler, Richard J, ed. \"The Cranial Osteology and Feeding Ecology of the Metriorhynchid Crocodylomorph Genera Dakosaurus and Plesiosuchus from the Late Jurassic of Europe | pmid = 23028723 | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 7 | issue = 9| page = e44985 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0044985 | pmc=3445579}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Martin | first1 = J. E. | last2 = Vincent | first2 = P. | year = 2013 | title = New remains of Machimosaurus hugii von Meyer, 1837 (Crocodilia, Thalattosuchia) from the Kimmeridgian of Germany | url = | journal = Fossil Record | volume = 16 | issue = | pages = 179\u2013196 | doi = 10.1002/mmng.201300009 }}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"180px\">\nSteneosaurus heberti skull.JPG|'''S.' heberti'' skull\nSteneosaurus bollensis Tubingen.JPG|'''S.' bollensis''\nSteneosaurus NT small.jpg|Reconstruction of '''S.' bollensis''\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Paleontology}}\n* [[List of marine reptiles]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Steneosaurus|''Steneosaurus''}}\n* [http://www.angellis.net/Web/PDfiles/repcrocs.pdf Angellis Net pdf]\n\n{{Thalattosuchia}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q137074}}\n\n[[Category:Thalattosuchians]]\n[[Category:Prehistoric reptile genera]]\n[[Category:Prehistoric marine crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Early Jurassic crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Middle Jurassic crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Aalenian life]]\n[[Category:Bajocian life]]\n[[Category:Bathonian life]]\n[[Category:Callovian life]]\n[[Category:Toarcian life]]\n[[Category:Early Jurassic reptiles of Europe]]\n[[Category:Middle Jurassic reptiles of Europe]]\n[[Category:Fossils of England]]\n[[Category:Oxford Clay]]\n[[Category:Fossils of France]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Germany]]\n[[Category:Solnhofen fauna]]\n[[Category:Jurassic reptiles of Africa]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Morocco]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Fossil taxa described in 1825]]\n[[Category:Nomina dubia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = [[Middle_Jurassic|Middle]] or [[Late Jurassic]]<br />~{{Fossil range|Callovian|Oxfordian|[[Callovian]] or Lower [[Oxfordian]]}}\n| image = Steneosaurus Holzmaden.jpg\n| image_caption = '''Steneosaurus' bollensis'', Holzmaden Germany\n| taxon = Steneosaurus\n| authority = [[\u00c9tienne Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire|Geoffroy]], 1825\n| type_species = {{extinct}} '''''Steneosaurus rostromajor'''''\n| type_species_authority = Geoffroy, 1825\n| subdivision_ranks = Assigned species\n| subdivision =\n* '''S.' baroni'' {{small|Newton 1893}}\n* '''S.' bollensis'' {{small|(Jaeger 1828)}}\n* '''S.' edwardsi'' {{small|(Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868)}}\n* '''S.' gracilirostris'' {{small|Westphal 1961}}\n* '''S.' heberti'' {{small|Morel de Glasville 1876}}\n* '''S.' leedsi'' {{small|Andrews 1909}}\n* '''S.' megistorhynchus'' {{small|(Geoffrey Saint-Hilaire in Eudes-Deslongchamps 1869)}}\n* '''S.' pictaviensis'' {{small|Vignaud 1998}}\n| synonyms =\n{{collapsible list|bullets = true\n |title=<small>'''Synonyms of ''Steneosaurus'''''</small>\n| ?''[[Macrospondylus]]'' {{small|[[Christian Erich Hermann von Meyer|Von Meyer]] 1830}}\n| ''Leptocranius'' {{small|Bronn 1837}} }}\n{{collapsible list|bullets = true\n |title=<small>'''Synonyms of ''S. rostromajor''''':</small>\n| ''Gavialis bacheleti''\n| ''Steneosaurus longirostris'' }}\n}}\n\n'''''Steneosaurus''''' is a [[Nomen_dubium|dubious]] [[genus]] of [[Teleosauridae|teleosaurid]] [[crocodyliform]] from the [[Middle Jurassic|Middle]] or [[Late Jurassic]] ([[Callovian]] or early [[Oxfordian]]) of [[France]]. The genus has been used as a [[wastebasket taxon]] for thalattosuchian fossils for over two centuries, and almost all known historical species of teleosauroid have been included within it at one point. The genus has remained a wastebasket, with numerous species still included under the label ''\u2018Steneosaurus\u2019'', many of which are unrelated to each other (either [[paraphyletic]] or [[polyphyletic]] with respect to each other and other genera of teleosauroids).\n\nThe [[type species]], '''''S. rostromajor''''', was only formally recognised as such in 2020, and this revision determined the [[type specimen]] of ''Steneosaurus'' was undiagnostic, and so declared the genus ''Steneosaurus'' a ''nomen dubium''. The remaining species referred to ''Steneosaurus'' thus require new generic names, and some species have already been assigned to new genera prior to ''Steneosaurus'' being declared a ''nomen dubium''.<ref name=\"revised\">{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=M. M. |last2=Young |first2=M. R. |last3=Brusatte |first3=S. L. |year=2020 |title=Emptying the wastebasket: a historical and taxonomic revision of the Jurassic crocodylomorph ''Steneosaurus'' |journal=Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society |issue=zlaa027 |doi=10.1093/zoolinnean/zlaa027}}</ref>\n== Species ==\n[[File:Steneosaurus durobrivensis 45.jpg|thumb|right|250px|'''S.' edwardsi'' skull]]\nSpecies in this genus are traditionally classed into two skull groups: longirostrine (long, narrow jaws) and mesorostrine (slightly shorter jaws).\n\n;Longirostrine\n* '''S.' atelestatus'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381015 ''Steneosaurus atelestatus''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Oxfordian [[Marnes de Villers Formation]] of France\n* '''S.' baroni'' - [[Bathonian]] [[Oolite Formation|Oolite]] and [[Kandreho Formation]]s of [[Madagascar]]\n* '''S.' blumembachi'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381016 ''Steneosaurus blumembachi''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Oxfordian Marnes de Villers Formation of France\n* '''S.' bollensis'' - Toarcian [[Alum Shale Formation|Alum Shale]] and [[Jet Rock Formation]]s of England and [[Posidonia Shale]] of Germany\n* '''S.' gracilirostris'' - Toarcian Alum Shale of England\n* '''S.' heberti'' - Callovian Etrochey vertebrate layer (C\u00f4te-d'Or) of France\n* '''S.' leedsi'' - Callovian Oxford Clay of England\n* '''S.' megistorhynchus'' ([[type species|type]]) - Bathonian [[Forest Marble Formation]] of England and Great Oolite Formation of France\n* '''S.' oplites'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1863<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=381014 ''Steneosaurus oplites''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - Toarcian La Caine-Curcy of France\n* '''S.' pictaviensis'' - Callovian Les Lourdines in France\n* '''S.' rudis'' {{small|Sauvage 1874<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=89217 ''Steneosaurus rudis''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref>}} - France\n\n;Mesorostrine\n* '''S.' bouchardi'' - {{small|Sauvage 1872}}, Kimmeridgian\u2013Tithonian of France\n* '''S.' edwardsi'' - Callovian [[Marnes de Dives]] Formation, Le Wast and Les Lourdines in France and [[Oxford Clay]] of England\n\nAdditional ''Steneosaurus'' fossils not attributed to a specific genus have been found in:\n* Bathonian [[El Mers Formation]], Morocco\n* Bathonian [[Techout Formation]], Tunisia\n* Jurassic Czarnoglowy, Poland\n\n=== Reassigned species ===\n* '''Steneosaurus' boutilieri'' {{small|Eudes-Deslongchamps 1869}} = ''[[Yvridiosuchus]]''<ref name=Johnson19>{{cite journal |last1=Johnson |first1=Michela M. |last2=Young |first2=Mark T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=Stephen L. |year=2019 |title=Re-description of two contemporaneous mesorostrine teleosauroids (Crocodylomorpha: Thalattosuchia) from the Bathonian of England and insights into the early evolution of Machimosaurini |journal=[[Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society]] |volume=in press |issue= |pages= |doi=10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz037 }}</ref>\n* '''Steneosaurus' brevior'' {{small|Blake, 1876}} = ''[[Mystriosaurus]]''\n* '''Steneosaurus' deslongchampsianus'' {{small|(Lennier 1887)<ref name=Foffa2018>{{cite journal |last=Foffa |first=Davide |last2=Young |first2=Mark T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=Stephen L. |year=2018 |title=Filling the Corallian gap: New information on Late Jurassic marine reptile faunas from England |url=http://www.app.pan.pl/archive/published/app63/app004552018.pdf |journal=[[Acta Palaeontologica Polonica]] |volume=63 |pages=287\u2013313 |accessdate=2019-03-07 |doi=10.4202/app.00455.2018}}</ref>}}\n* '''Steneosaurus' larteti'' {{small|(Eudes-Deslongchamps 1868)}} = ''[[Deslongchampsina]]''<ref name=Johnson19/>\n* '''Steneosaurus' megarhinus'' {{small|(Hulke 1871)}} = ''[[Bathysuchus]]''<ref>{{cite journal |last=Foffa |first=D. |last2=Young |first2=M.T. |last3=Brusatte |first3=S.L. |last4=Steel |first4=L. |year=2015 |title=New specimen and revision of the late Jurassic teleosaurid 'Steneosaurus' megarhinus |url=https://peerj.com/preprints/1351/ |journal=[[PeerJ Preprints]] |volume=3 |pages=e1351v1 |accessdate=2019-03-07}}</ref><ref name=Foffa19>{{cite journal |last1=Foffa |first1=D. |last2=Johnson |first2=M.M. |last3=Young|first3=M.T. |last4=Steel |first4=L. |last5=Brusatte |first5=S.L. |date=2019 |title=Revision of the Late Jurassic deep-water teleosauroid crocodylomorph ''Teleosaurus megarhinus'' Hulke, 1871 and evidence of pelagic adaptations in Teleosauroidea. |journal=[[PeerJ]] |volume=7 |pages=e6646 |doi=10.7717/peerj.6646 |pmid=30972249 |pmc=6450380}}</ref>\n* '''Steneosaurus' obtusidens'' {{small|Andrews 1909}} = ''[[Lemmysuchus]]''\n\n== Evolutionary relationships ==\nA 2005 [[phylogenetic]] analysis into the evolutionary relationships of [[Thalattosuchia]] did not support the [[monophyly]] of ''Steneosaurus'', as the genera ''[[Machimosaurus]]'' and ''[[Teleosaurus]]'' both fell within ''Steneosaurus''.<ref name=\"Mueller-T\u00f6we, 2005\">{{cite journal |last=Mueller-T\u00f6we |first=I. J. |year=2005 |title=Phylogenetic relationships of the Thalattosuchia |journal=Zitteliana |volume=A45 |issue= |pages=211\u2013213 |url=http://epub.ub.uni-muenchen.de/11958/1/zitteliana_2005_45_09.pdf }}</ref> Reinforcing the paraphyly of ''Steneosaurus'', the Callovian species ''\"Steneosaurus\" obtusidens'' has been recovered as the sister species of ''Machimosaurus'' in recent cladistic analyses of Thalattosuchia and renamed ''[[Lemmysuchus]]'', while '''Steneosaurus' bollensis'' was recovered in a basal position to other members of ''Steneosaurus sensu lato''.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = M. T. | last2 = Brusatte | first2 = S. L. | last3 = De Andrade | first3 = M. B. | last4 = Desojo | first4 = J. B. | last5 = Beatty | first5 = B. L. | last6 = Steel | first6 = L. | last7 = Fern\u00e1ndez | first7 = M. S. | last8 = Sakamoto | first8 = M. | last9 = Ruiz-Ome\u00f1aca | first9 = J. I. | last10 = Schoch | first10 = R. R. | year = 2012 | title = \"Butler, Richard J, ed. \"The Cranial Osteology and Feeding Ecology of the Metriorhynchid Crocodylomorph Genera Dakosaurus and Plesiosuchus from the Late Jurassic of Europe | pmid = 23028723 | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 7 | issue = 9| page = e44985 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0044985 | pmc=3445579}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Martin | first1 = J. E. | last2 = Vincent | first2 = P. | year = 2013 | title = New remains of Machimosaurus hugii von Meyer, 1837 (Crocodilia, Thalattosuchia) from the Kimmeridgian of Germany | url = | journal = Fossil Record | volume = 16 | issue = | pages = 179\u2013196 | doi = 10.1002/mmng.201300009 }}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"180px\">\nSteneosaurus heberti skull.JPG|'''S.' heberti'' skull\nSteneosaurus bollensis Tubingen.JPG|'''S.' bollensis''\nSteneosaurus NT small.jpg|Reconstruction of '''S.' bollensis''\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Paleontology}}\n* [[List of marine reptiles]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Steneosaurus|''Steneosaurus''}}\n* [http://www.angellis.net/Web/PDfiles/repcrocs.pdf Angellis Net pdf]\n\n{{Thalattosuchia}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q137074}}\n\n[[Category:Thalattosuchians]]\n[[Category:Prehistoric reptile genera]]\n[[Category:Prehistoric marine crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Early Jurassic crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Middle Jurassic crocodylomorphs]]\n[[Category:Aalenian life]]\n[[Category:Bajocian life]]\n[[Category:Bathonian life]]\n[[Category:Callovian life]]\n[[Category:Toarcian life]]\n[[Category:Early Jurassic reptiles of Europe]]\n[[Category:Middle Jurassic reptiles of Europe]]\n[[Category:Fossils of England]]\n[[Category:Oxford Clay]]\n[[Category:Fossils of France]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Germany]]\n[[Category:Solnhofen fauna]]\n[[Category:Jurassic reptiles of Africa]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Morocco]]\n[[Category:Fossils of Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Fossil taxa described in 1825]]\n[[Category:Nomina dubia]]\n", "name_user": "DrawingDinosaurs", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Oxfordian\u2192Oxfordian (stage)(2) usingDab solveri", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steneosaurus"}
{"title_page": "White on White (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = White on White\n| image          = Blanco en blanco film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Th\u00e9o Court]]\n| studio         = El Viaje Films (Spain)<br>Quijote Films (Chile)\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Th\u00e9o Court<br>Samuel M. Delgado\n| starring       = [[Alfredo Castro (actor)|Alfredo Castro]]<br>[[Lars Rudolph]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2019|09|02|[[76th Venice International Film Festival|Venice]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 100 minutes\n| country        = Spain<br>Chile\n| language       = Spanish<br>English\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''White on White''''' ({{lang-es|'''Blanco en blanco'''}}) is a 2019 Spanish-Chilean [[drama film]] directed by [[Th\u00e9o Court]]. It was screened in the Horizons section at the [[76th Venice International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/venice-film-festival-lineup-the-truth-ad-astra-marriage-story-1203277662/|title=Joker, Ad Astra, The Laundromat, Marriage Story to Compete in Venice|last=Vivarelli|first=Nick|work=Variety|date=25 July 2019|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2019/orizzonti|title=Orizzonti|publisher=labiennale.org|date=25 July 2019|accessdate=28 July 2019}}</ref> At the Venice Film Festival, Th\u00e9o Court won the award for Best Director in the Horizons section.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-awards-revealed-1237684 |title=Venice: Todd Phillips' 'Joker' Wins Golden Lion, Roman Polanski Wins Silver Lion |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Ariston |last=Anderson |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Alfredo Castro (actor)|Alfredo Castro]]\n* [[Lars Rudolph]]\n* [[Lola Rubio]]\n* [[David Pantale\u00f3n]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|9028522|White on White}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:White On White}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 drama films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:Spanish drama films]]\n[[Category:Chilean films]]\n[[Category:Chilean drama films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Spain]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Spain]]\n[[Category:Films set in Chile]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Chile]]\n{{2010s-Spain-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = White on White\n| image          = Blanco en blanco film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Th\u00e9o Court]]\n| studio         = El Viaje Films (Spain)<br>Quijote Films (Chile)\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Th\u00e9o Court<br>Samuel M. Delgado\n| starring       = [[Alfredo Castro (actor)|Alfredo Castro]]<br>[[Lars Rudolph]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2019|09|02|[[76th Venice International Film Festival|Venice]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 100 minutes\n| country        = Spain<br>Chile\n| language       = Spanish<br>English\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''White on White''''' ({{lang-es|'''Blanco en blanco'''}}) is a 2019 Spanish-Chilean [[drama film]] directed by [[Th\u00e9o Court]]. It was screened in the Horizons section at the [[76th Venice International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/venice-film-festival-lineup-the-truth-ad-astra-marriage-story-1203277662/|title=Joker, Ad Astra, The Laundromat, Marriage Story to Compete in Venice|last=Vivarelli|first=Nick|work=Variety|date=25 July 2019|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2019/orizzonti|title=Orizzonti|publisher=lab