{"title_page": "Paul Bosvelt", "text_new": "{{short description|Dutch former professional footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Paul Bosvelt\n| image          = Paul bosvelt.jpg\n| image_size     = 200px\n| caption        = Paul Bosvelt\n| alt            =\n| fullname       = Paul Bosvelt\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|3|26}}\n| birth_place    = [[Doetinchem]], Netherlands\n| height         = 1.83 m\n| position       = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]\n| years1         = 1989\u20131994 |clubs1 = [[Go Ahead Eagles]]                      |caps1 = 139 |goals1 = 27\n| years2         = 1994\u20131997 |clubs2 = [[FC Twente|Twente]]                     |caps2 = 96  |goals2 = 21\n| years3         = 1997\u20132003 |clubs3 = [[Feyenoord]]                            |caps3 = 177 |goals3 = 33\n| years4         = 2003\u20132005 |clubs4 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |caps4 = 53  |goals4 = 2\n| years5         = 2005\u20132007 |clubs5 = [[SC Heerenveen]]                        |caps5 = 58  |goals5 = 5\n| totalcaps      = 523 |totalgoals = 88\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132004<ref>{{Cite news|title=Paul Bosvelt - International Appearances|publisher=The Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bosvelt-intl.html}}</ref> |nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] |nationalcaps1 = 24 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{medal|Country|{{fb|NED}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[UEFA European Championship]]|}}\n{{Medal|B|[[UEFA Euro 2000|2000 Belgium-Netherlands]]|}}\n{{Medal|B|[[UEFA Euro 2004|2004 Portugal]]|}}\n}}\n'''Paul Bosvelt''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8p\u028cul \u02c8b\u0254sf\u025blt}}, born 26 March 1970) is a Dutch former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]]. He played for [[Go Ahead Eagles]] and [[FC Twente|Twente]] before moving to [[Feyenoord]] in 1997. After six seasons with Feyenoord he joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. Two years later, he returned to the Netherlands spending two seasons at [[SC Heerenveen]] before retiring.\n\n==Club career==\nBosvelt went on to develop a reputation as a fearsome midfield general at [[Feijenoord Stadion|de Kuip]], making 167 appearances, during which he led Feyenoord to the [[Eredivisie|league title]] in 1999 and won the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]].\n\nIn 2003, Bosvelt joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]],<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/paul-bosvelt-voor-twee-jaar-naar-man-city.htm Paul Bosvelt voor twee jaar naar Man City] - Voetbal International {{in lang|nl}}</ref> where he played an important role in the team. However, after two seasons he returned to Netherlands where he finished his career at [[SC Heerenveen]].<ref>[http://www.sc-heerenveen.nl/nieuws/sc-heerenveen-contracteert-paul-bosvelt/10 sc Heerenveen contracteert Paul Bosvelt] - Heerenveen {{in lang|nl}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBosvelt made his debut for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in a March 2000 [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] and earned a total of 24 caps, scoring no goals.<ref>[http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/11/5579777d-6d5af161-712891 Intl career stats] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105162559/http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/11/5579777d-6d5af161-712891 |date=5 November 2016 }} - Ons Oranje {{in lang|nl}}</ref> He played in [[UEFA Euro 2000|Euro 2000]] and [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]]. During Euro 2000, he reached the semi-final with Netherlands. Bosvelt missed an important penalty kick in the penalty shootout in the semi-finals, which led to a 3\u20131 defeat against [[Italy national football team|Italy]]. After Euro 2004 he decided to retire from international football.\n\n==Retirement==\nBosvelt retired from football on 13 May 2007, after a 4\u20130 defeat against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]. He played a total number of 470 games in both [[Eredivisie]] and [[Eerste Divisie]].\n\nIn summer 2016 Bosvelt was named coach at Jong FC Twente next to his position as an assistant at Netherlands U-21.<ref>[http://www.rtvoost.nl/sport/default.aspx?nid=246067 Paul Bosvelt trainer van de beloften van FC Twente] - RTV Oost {{in lang|nl}}</ref>.\nSince april 2018 Bosvelt is technical manager at [[Go Ahead Eagles]].\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Feyenoord'''\n* [[Eredivisie|Dutch National League]]: 1999\n* [[Dutch Super Cup]]: 2000\n* [[UEFA Cup]]: [[2001\u201302 UEFA Cup|2002]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT|4662}}\n* [http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football-heroes/searchresults.asp?FootballHeroName=Paul+Bosvelt Photos and stats] at sporting-heroes.net\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|bg= #F1771D\n|fg= white\n|title= Netherlands squads\n|list1=\n{{Netherlands Squad 2000 UEFA Euro}}\n{{Netherlands Squad - Euro 2004}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bosvelt, Paul}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Doetinchem]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Netherlands international footballers]]\n[[Category:Go Ahead Eagles players]]\n[[Category:FC Twente players]]\n[[Category:Feyenoord players]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:SC Heerenveen players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2000 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2004 players]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Dutch former professional footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Paul Bosvelt\n| image          = Paul bosvelt.jpg\n| image_size     = 200px\n| caption        =\n| alt            =\n| fullname       = Paul Bosvelt\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|3|26}}\n| birth_place    = [[Doetinchem]], Netherlands\n| height         = 1.83 m\n| position       = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]\n| years1         = 1989\u20131994 |clubs1 = [[Go Ahead Eagles]]                      |caps1 = 139 |goals1 = 27\n| years2         = 1994\u20131997 |clubs2 = [[FC Twente|Twente]]                     |caps2 = 96  |goals2 = 21\n| years3         = 1997\u20132003 |clubs3 = [[Feyenoord]]                            |caps3 = 177 |goals3 = 33\n| years4         = 2003\u20132005 |clubs4 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |caps4 = 53  |goals4 = 2\n| years5         = 2005\u20132007 |clubs5 = [[SC Heerenveen]]                        |caps5 = 58  |goals5 = 5\n| totalcaps      = 523 |totalgoals = 88\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132004<ref>{{Cite news|title=Paul Bosvelt - International Appearances|publisher=The Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bosvelt-intl.html}}</ref> |nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] |nationalcaps1 = 24 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{medal|Country|{{fb|NED}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[UEFA European Championship]]|}}\n{{Medal|B|[[UEFA Euro 2000|2000 Belgium-Netherlands]]|}}\n{{Medal|B|[[UEFA Euro 2004|2004 Portugal]]|}}\n}}\n'''Paul Bosvelt''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8p\u028cul \u02c8b\u0254sf\u025blt}}, born 26 March 1970) is a Dutch former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]]. He played for [[Go Ahead Eagles]] and [[FC Twente|Twente]] before moving to [[Feyenoord]] in 1997. After six seasons with Feyenoord he joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. Two years later, he returned to the Netherlands spending two seasons at [[SC Heerenveen]] before retiring.\n\n==Club career==\nBosvelt went on to develop a reputation as a fearsome midfield general at [[Feijenoord Stadion|de Kuip]], making 167 appearances, during which he led Feyenoord to the [[Eredivisie|league title]] in 1999 and won the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]].\n\nIn 2003, Bosvelt joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]],<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/paul-bosvelt-voor-twee-jaar-naar-man-city.htm Paul Bosvelt voor twee jaar naar Man City] - Voetbal International {{in lang|nl}}</ref> where he played an important role in the team. However, after two seasons he returned to Netherlands where he finished his career at [[SC Heerenveen]].<ref>[http://www.sc-heerenveen.nl/nieuws/sc-heerenveen-contracteert-paul-bosvelt/10 sc Heerenveen contracteert Paul Bosvelt] - Heerenveen {{in lang|nl}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBosvelt made his debut for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in a March 2000 [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] and earned a total of 24 caps, scoring no goals.<ref>[http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/11/5579777d-6d5af161-712891 Intl career stats] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105162559/http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/11/5579777d-6d5af161-712891 |date=5 November 2016 }} - Ons Oranje {{in lang|nl}}</ref> He played in [[UEFA Euro 2000|Euro 2000]] and [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]]. During Euro 2000, he reached the semi-final with Netherlands. Bosvelt missed an important penalty kick in the penalty shootout in the semi-finals, which led to a 3\u20131 defeat against [[Italy national football team|Italy]]. After Euro 2004 he decided to retire from international football.\n\n==Retirement==\nBosvelt retired from football on 13 May 2007, after a 4\u20130 defeat against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]. He played a total number of 470 games in both [[Eredivisie]] and [[Eerste Divisie]].\n\nIn summer 2016 Bosvelt was named coach at Jong FC Twente next to his position as an assistant at Netherlands U-21.<ref>[http://www.rtvoost.nl/sport/default.aspx?nid=246067 Paul Bosvelt trainer van de beloften van FC Twente] - RTV Oost {{in lang|nl}}</ref>.\nSince april 2018 Bosvelt is technical manager at [[Go Ahead Eagles]].\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Feyenoord'''\n* [[Eredivisie|Dutch National League]]: 1999\n* [[Dutch Super Cup]]: 2000\n* [[UEFA Cup]]: [[2001\u201302 UEFA Cup|2002]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT|4662}}\n* [http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football-heroes/searchresults.asp?FootballHeroName=Paul+Bosvelt Photos and stats] at sporting-heroes.net\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|bg= #F1771D\n|fg= white\n|title= Netherlands squads\n|list1=\n{{Netherlands Squad 2000 UEFA Euro}}\n{{Netherlands Squad - Euro 2004}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bosvelt, Paul}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Doetinchem]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Netherlands international footballers]]\n[[Category:Go Ahead Eagles players]]\n[[Category:FC Twente players]]\n[[Category:Feyenoord players]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:SC Heerenveen players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2000 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2004 players]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Add image caption.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Bosvelt"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Artsakh", "text_new": "{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the So-called Republic of Nagorno Karabakh\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| map1            = File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Artsakh (Density).svg\n| legend1         = Number of confirmed cases by province (as of 8 April): {{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1\u20139}}<!--{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 10\u201349}}{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 50\u2013199}}{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 200\u2013499}}{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 500\u2013999}}{{legend|#630606|Confirmed \u22651,000}}-->\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Karabakh]]\n| first_case      = [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]], [[LachinProvince]]\n| arrival_date    = 7 April 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=04|day1=07|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Karabakh]], [[Azerbaijan]]\n| recovery_cases  = 0\n| deaths          = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 5\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread in April 2020 to the So-called Republic of Nagorno Karabakh(a ''de-facto'' independent republic on territory ''de-jure'' part of [[Azerbaijan]]). The first infected person was from the village of [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]] in the province of Lachinwho contracted the virus from Armenia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/04/07/artsakh-coronavirus/1681590|title=First coronavirus case recorded in Artsakh - aysor.am - Hot news from Armenia|last=LLC|first=Helix Consulting|website=www.aysor.am|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019-20 coronavirus pandemic data/Republic of Artsakh cases chart}}\n\n=== March ===\nThe border of the Republic of Artsakh with [[Armenia]] has been closed in order to prevent the virus from spreading to the unrecognized republic, which had its [[2020 Artsakhian general election|general elections]] on 31 March.\n=== April ===\n\nOn 7 April, the Ministry of Health of the Artsakh Republic reported about its first coronavirus case after one of two suspected case tested positive for Covid-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/571021.html|title=First coronavirus case reported in Karabakh|website=news.am|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> The person is from [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]].\n\nOn 9 April, three people were tested, of whom two tested positive for COVID-19, though one of them is a citizen of [[Armenia]]. The local who tested positive had registered to vote in [[Moshatagh]] (near Mirik).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/571557.html|title=2 out of 3 citizens tested for coronavirus in Artsakh have positive results|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At this point, all known cases in Artsakh were from the province of [[Kashatagh Province|Kashatagh]].\n\nOn 10 April, one of the two additional confirmed cases was from [[Karvachar]], [[Shahumyan Province|Shahumyan]], making it the second province in Artsakh to have a confirmed case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.evnreport.com/covid-19/covid-19-daily-briefing-april-10|title=COVID-19 Daily Briefing (April 10)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{Graph:Chart\n | type = rect\n | width = 680\n | colors = #ff6346\n | legend = Legend\n | showValues = offset:2\n | xAxisTitle = Date\n | xAxisAngle = -40\n | yAxisTitle = No. of new cases\n | y1Title = New cases per day\n | x = 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr\n | y1 = 1, 0, 2, 2\n}}\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Republic of Artsakh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Artsakh\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| map1            = File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Artsakh (Density).svg\n| legend1         = Number of confirmed cases by province (as of 8 April): {{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1\u20139}}<!--{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 10\u201349}}{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 50\u2013199}}{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 200\u2013499}}{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 500\u2013999}}{{legend|#630606|Confirmed \u22651,000}}-->\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Republic of Artsakh|Artsakh]]\n| first_case      = [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]], [[Kashatagh Province]]\n| arrival_date    = 7 April 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=04|day1=07|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Artashat, Armenia|Artashat]], [[Armenia]]\n| recovery_cases  = 0\n| deaths          = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 5\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|moh.nkr.am}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread in April 2020 to the [[Republic of Artsakh]] (a ''de-facto'' independent republic on territory ''de-jure'' part of [[Azerbaijan]]). The first infected person was from the village of [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]] in the province of [[Kashatagh Province|Kashatagh]] who contracted the virus from [[Armenia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/04/07/artsakh-coronavirus/1681590|title=First coronavirus case recorded in Artsakh - aysor.am - Hot news from Armenia|last=LLC|first=Helix Consulting|website=www.aysor.am|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019-20 coronavirus pandemic data/Republic of Artsakh cases chart}}\n\n=== March ===\nThe border of the Republic of Artsakh with [[Armenia]] has been closed in order to prevent the virus from spreading to the unrecognized republic, which had its [[2020 Artsakhian general election|general elections]] on 31 March.\n=== April ===\n\nOn 7 April, the Ministry of Health of the Artsakh Republic reported about its first coronavirus case after one of two suspected case tested positive for Covid-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/571021.html|title=First coronavirus case reported in Karabakh|website=news.am|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> The person is from [[Mirik, Azerbaijan|Mirik]].\n\nOn 9 April, three people were tested, of whom two tested positive for COVID-19, though one of them is a citizen of [[Armenia]]. The local who tested positive had registered to vote in [[Moshatagh]] (near Mirik).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.am/eng/news/571557.html|title=2 out of 3 citizens tested for coronavirus in Artsakh have positive results|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At this point, all known cases in Artsakh were from the province of [[Kashatagh Province|Kashatagh]].\n\nOn 10 April, one of the two additional confirmed cases was from [[Karvachar]], [[Shahumyan Province|Shahumyan]], making it the second province in Artsakh to have a confirmed case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.evnreport.com/covid-19/covid-19-daily-briefing-april-10|title=COVID-19 Daily Briefing (April 10)|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{Graph:Chart\n | type = rect\n | width = 680\n | colors = #ff6346\n | legend = Legend\n | showValues = offset:2\n | xAxisTitle = Date\n | xAxisAngle = -40\n | yAxisTitle = No. of new cases\n | y1Title = New cases per day\n | x = 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr\n | y1 = 1, 0, 2, 2\n}}\n\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Artsakh]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Republic of Artsakh]]\n", "name_user": "Xalid H\u0259s\u0259nli", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Republic_of_Artsakh"}
