l \u2026\u2019 \u2013 Album Review|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/trace-adkins-love-will/|accessdate=May 15, 2013|newspaper=Taste of Country|date=May 14, 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Love Will...''''' is the fourteenth studio album by American [[country music]] artist [[Trace Adkins]]. It was released on May 14, 2013 via [[Show Dog-Universal Music]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Bjorke|first=Matt|title=Trace Adkins \"Love Will...\" Tracklist and Cover Art|url=http://www.roughstock.com/blog/trace-adkins-love-will-tracklist-and-cover-art|accessdate=May 15, 2013|newspaper=Roughstock|date=March 25, 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130630062533/http://www.roughstock.com/blog/trace-adkins-love-will-tracklist-and-cover-art|archive-date=June 30, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album features collaborations with [[Colbie Caillat]], [[Exile (American band)|Exile]] and the [[Harlem Gospel Choir]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Wyland|first=Sarah|title=Colbie Caillat & Exile Featured on Trace Adkins\u2019 New Album|url=http://blog.gactv.com/blog/2013/03/28/colbie-caillat-exile-featured-on-trace-adkins-new-album/|accessdate=May 15, 2013|newspaper=[[Great American Country]]|date=March 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = 41:38\n| title1          = When I Stop Loving You\n| writer1         = [[Marty Brown (singer)|Marty Brown]], Even Stevens\n| length1         = 3:21\n| title2          = So What If I Do\n| writer2         = Ward Davis, Rick Huckaby, Matt Nolan\n| length2         = 3:25\n| title3          = Come See Me\n| writer3         = [[Kenny Beard]], Sonny LeMaire, [[J.P. Pennington]]\n| length3         = 2:58\n| title4          = Right Now\n| writer4         = Beard, Aly Cutter, Nolan\n| length4         = 3:10\n| title5          = Every One of You\n| writer5         = Steve Bogard, [[Kyle Jacobs]], [[Billy Montana]], Phil O'Donnell\n| length5         = 3:15\n| title6          = The Altar of Your Love\n| writer6         = Trace Adkins, Beard, Monty Criswell\n| length6         = 3:32\n| title7          = [[Kiss You All Over]]\n| note7           = featuring [[Exile (American band)|Exile]]\n| writer7         = [[Mike Chapman]], [[Nicky Chinn]]\n| length7         = 5:13\n| title8          = If the Sun Comes Up\n| writer8         = [[Ray Scott (singer)|Ray Scott]], George Teren\n| length8         = 4:30\n| title9          = Say No to a Woman\n| writer9         = [[Lee Thomas Miller]], [[Jimmy Yeary]]\n| length9         = 3:39\n| title10         = Watch the World End\n| note10          = featuring [[Colbie Caillat]]\n| writer10        = [[Brett Eldredge]], Jeremy Spillman\n| length10        = 4:39\n| title11         = Love Will\n| note11          = featuring the [[Harlem Gospel Choir]]\n| writer11        = [[Tim James (country music songwriter)|Tim James]], [[Chris Stapleton]]\n| length11        = 3:56\n}}\n\n*[https://www.techytechs.in/story-of-failed-person-station/ KFC Owner]\n*[[Trace Adkins]] - lead vocals\n*David Angell - [[violin]]\n*The Beagles - background vocals\n*Mike Brignardello - [[bass guitar]]\n*[[Pat Buchanan (musician)|Pat Buchanan]] - [[electric guitar]]\n*[[Colbie Caillat]] - vocals on \"Watch The World End\"\n*Jimmy Carter - bass guitar\n*Wei Tsun Chung - violin\n*[[Mickey Jack Cones]] - [[acoustic guitar]], electric guitar, [[percussion]], background vocals\n*[[J.T. Corenflos]] - electric guitar\n*[[Chad Cromwell]] - [[drums]]\n*Aly Cutter - background vocals\n*[[Eric Darken]] - percussion\n*Shawn Fichter - drums\n*[[Shannon Forrest]] - drums\n*Steve Goetzman - drums on \"Kiss You All Over\"\n*Marlon Hargis - [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]] on \"Kiss You All Over\"\n*Harlem Gospel Choir - background vocals on \"Love Will\"\n*Tony Harrell - keyboards\n*[[Aubrey Haynie]] - [[fiddle]], [[mandolin]]\n*Wes Hightower - background vocals\n*Mark Hill - bass guitar\n*Jim Hoke - [[saxophone]]\n*[[John Barlow Jarvis]] - [[piano]]\n*Mike Johnson - [[pedal steel guitar]]\n*Charlie Judge - keyboards\n*Troy Lancast