nd Cover Art|url=http://www.roughstock.com/blog/trace-adkins-love-will-tracklist-and-cover-art|accessdate=May 15, 2013|newspaper=Roughstock|date=March 25, 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130630062533/http://www.roughstock.com/blog/trace-adkins-love-will-tracklist-and-cover-art|archive-date=June 30, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album features collaborations with [[Colbie Caillat]], [[Exile (American band)|Exile]] and the [[Harlem Gospel Choir]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Wyland|first=Sarah|title=Colbie Caillat & Exile Featured on Trace Adkins\u2019 New Album|url=http://blog.gactv.com/blog/2013/03/28/colbie-caillat-exile-featured-on-trace-adkins-new-album/|accessdate=May 15, 2013|newspaper=[[Great American Country]]|date=March 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = 41:38\n| title1          = When I Stop Loving You\n| writer1         = [[Marty Brown (singer)|Marty Brown]], Even Stevens\n| length1         = 3:21\n| title2          = So What If I Do\n| writer2         = Ward Davis, Rick Huckaby, Matt Nolan\n| length2         = 3:25\n| title3          = Come See Me\n| writer3         = [[Kenny Beard]], Sonny LeMaire, [[J.P. Pennington]]\n| length3         = 2:58\n| title4          = Right Now\n| writer4         = Beard, Aly Cutter, Nolan\n| length4         = 3:10\n| title5          = Every One of You\n| writer5         = Steve Bogard, [[Kyle Jacobs]], [[Billy Montana]], Phil O'Donnell\n| length5         = 3:15\n| title6          = The Altar of Your Love\n| writer6         = Trace Adkins, Beard, Monty Criswell\n| length6         = 3:32\n| title7          = [[Kiss You All Over]]\n| note7           = featuring [[Exile (American band)|Exile]]\n| writer7         = [[Mike Chapman]], [[Nicky Chinn]]\n| length7         = 5:13\n| title8          = If the Sun Comes Up\n| writer8         = [[Ray Scott (singer)|Ray Scott]], George Teren\n| length8         = 4:30\n| title9          = Say No to a Woman\n| writer9         = [[Lee Thomas Miller]], [[