e.org/web/20090508115750/http://www.olympic-museum.de/o-reports/report1992.htm Official Report]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090828040533/http://todor66.com/olim/1992/Athletics/Men_Shot_Put.html Results]\n\n{{OlympicsShotPut}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics - Men's shot put}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics|S]]\n[[Category:Shot put at the Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's shot put\n|games = 1992 Summer\n|image = Athletics pictogram.svg\n|image_size = 50px\n|caption = Pictogram for athletics\n|dates = July 31 (qualification and final)\n|venues = [[Estadi Ol\u00edmpic Llu\u00eds Companys|Estadi Ol\u00edmpic de Montju\u00efc]]\n|competitors = 27\n|nations = 18\n|longnames = yes\n|win_label = Winning distance\n|win_value = 21.70\n|gold = [[Mike Stulce]]\n|goldNOC = USA\n|silver = [[Jim Doehring]]\n|silverNOC = USA\n|bronze = [[Vyacheslav Lykho]]\n|bronzeNOC = EUN\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's shot put|1988]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's shot put|1996]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1992SummerOlympics}}\n\nThese are the official results of the '''[[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics|men's shot put]]''' event at the '''[[1992 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Barcelona, Spain]]. There were a total number of 27 participating athletes. The event took place on 31 July 1992.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1992/ATH/mens-shot-put.html |title=Athletics at the 1992 Barcelona Summer Games: Men's Shot Put |accessdate=8 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\nGold medalist [[Mike Stulce]] had returned from a 1990 two-year doping ban just in time to win the gold medal at the Barcelona Olympics. He subsequently failed another doping test at the 1993 World Outdoor Championships and received a life ban. Silver medallist [[Jim Doehring]], who had a guilty finding to a previous doping case overturned on a legal technicality, later tested positive for a banned steroids. Bronze medallist [[Vyacheslav Lykho]] had been stripped of his bronze medal won at the [[1990 European Athletics Championships|1990 European Championships]] in Split due to a doping offence.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/olympics-barcelona-1992-athletics-a-clean-sweep-for-former-drug-takers-1537525.html|title=OLYMPICS / Barcelona 1992: Athletics: A clean sweep for former drug takers|date=1 August 1992}}</ref> Despite this, they result from the Barcelona is officially accepted, because there is no known positive result from this games, and according to \"innocent until caught at that moment\" rule they can keep his medal.\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Mike Stulce]]|USA|1992 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Jim Doehring]]|USA|1992 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Vyacheslav Lykho]]|EUN|1992 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Abbreviations==\n*''All results shown are in metres''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"| '''Q''' || automatic qualification\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"| '''q''' || qualification by rank\n|-\n|'''DNS''' || did not start\n|-\n|'''NM''' || no mark\n|-\n|'''OR''' || olympic record\n|-\n|'''WR''' || world record\n|-\n|'''AR''' || area record\n|-\n|'''NR''' || national record\n|-\n|'''PB''' || personal best\n|-\n|'''SB''' || season best\n|}\n\n==Records==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"|Standing records prior to the 1992 Summer Olympics\n|-\n| [[List of world records in athletics|World Record]] || {{flagathlete|[[Randy Barnes]]|USA}} || '''23.12 m '''|| May 20, 1990 || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]], [[United States]] \n|-\n| [[List of Olympic records in athletics|Olympic Record]] || {{flagIOCat